<h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>How much car insurance do I actually need?</h3>
<p>At a minimum, you need to meet your state's legal requirements. However, most financial advisors recommend at least 100/300/100 liability limits to adequately protect your assets. If you have a newer vehicle, comprehensive and collision coverage is also recommended.</p>

<h3>Is the cheapest insurance always the best choice?</h3>
<p>Not necessarily. The cheapest policy may have higher deductibles, limited coverage, or come from a company with poor claims handling. The goal is to find the best value, meaning adequate coverage from a reputable company at a competitive price.</p>

<h3>How often should I shop for car insurance?</h3>
<p>At least once a year, ideally 2-4 weeks before your policy renews. You should also re-shop after major life events like moving, getting married, buying a new car, or having a ticket or accident fall off your record.</p>

<h3>Can I switch insurance companies mid-policy?</h3>
<p>Yes. Most car insurance policies can be canceled at any time without penalty. Some companies charge a small cancellation fee, but many do not. Just make sure your new policy starts before your old one ends to avoid a coverage gap.</p>
